      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OPTIMUS PRIME (8) trialled well coming into his fresh run but didn't fire at Belmont when right in the market as a $4.40 chance. Now he takes on the older horses, but he should be better for that effort and he comes right back to maiden company. Can get the job done this time around. LOVESEXY (5) has missed narrowly in both runs this time in, going under by 1.2L to a smart one last start. Third-up now and with some time between runs, she looks set to go to another level. Can go one better. MAD SPITFIRE (2) missed out in a tight finish here last week over 1400m, beaten 0.1L despite finishing third. Should be up front from the outset with Riordan's claim and can make a statement. PACIFIC LASS (7) hasn't trialled this time in work but has shown some talent in her previous heats. Can play a leading role on debut. HE'S A FIRECRACKER (3) won't be far away.",
